  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I recover a Yahoo hacked email address?",
  "response": "If you believe your Yahoo email address has been hacked, it's important to act quickly to secure your account and prevent further unauthorized access. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide to recover your hacked Yahoo email address:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Try to Log In**\n- Go to the Yahoo login page: [https://login.yahoo.com](https://login.yahoo.com).\n- Enter your email address and try to log in with your current password.\n- If your password has been changed, you won\u2019t be able to log in. Proceed to step 2.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Recover Your Yahoo Account**\n- Go to Yahoo\u2019s account recovery page: [https://login.yahoo.com/account/recovery](https://login.yahoo.com/account/recovery).\n- Enter your email address and click **Next**.\n- Follow the prompts to verify your identity. Yahoo will offer several recovery options:\n  - **Recovery Email:** If you\u2019ve set up a recovery email, Yahoo will send a verification code to that address.\n  - **Recovery Phone Number:** If you\u2019ve linked a phone number, Yahoo will send a verification code via SMS or call.\n  - **Security Questions:** Answer the security questions you set up when creating the account.\n  - **Alternate Email:** Use an alternate email address Yahoo has on file.\n- Once verified, you\u2019ll be able to reset your password.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Reset Your Password**\n- Create a strong, unique password that you haven\u2019t used before.\n- Avoid using easily guessable information (e.g., birthdays, names, etc.).\n- Yahoo requires passwords to be at least 8 characters long and include a mix of letters, numbers, and symbols.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Secure Your Account**\nAfter regaining access, take steps to secure your account:\n- **Update Recovery Information:** Add or update your recovery email and phone number.\n- **Enable Two-Factor Authentication (2FA):** Go to **Account Security** settings and enable 2FA for added security.\n- **Check Account Activity:** Review recent activity to ensure no unauthorized access. Yahoo allows you to see recent sign-ins with details like date, time, and location.\n- **Scan for Malware:** Check your computer or device for malware that may have compromised your account.\n- **Update Other Accounts:** If you use the same password for other accounts, change those passwords immediately.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Report the Hack to Yahoo**\nIf you\u2019re unable to recover your account or suspect ongoing unauthorized access, contact Yahoo Support:\n- Visit the Yahoo Help page: [https://help.yahoo.com](https://help.yahoo.com).\n- Use the **Contact Us** option to report the issue.\n- Provide as much information as possible to prove ownership of the account.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Prevent Future Hacks**\n- Avoid clicking on suspicious links or attachments in emails.\n- Use a unique password for each online account.\n- Regularly update your passwords and enable 2FA whenever possible.\n- Be cautious of phishing attempts. Yahoo will never ask for your password via email or phone.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to recover your hacked Yahoo account and secure it against future attacks.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
